114 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLISensorStart (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
115 {
116  bool doReconfig = true;
117  int32_t retVal = 0;
118 
119  /* Only following command syntax will be supported
120  sensorStart
121  sensorStart 0
122  */
123  if (argc == 2)
124  {
125  doReconfig = (bool) atoi (argv[1]);
126 
127  if (doReconfig == true)
128  {
129  CLI_write ("Error: Reconfig is not supported, only argument of 0 is\n"
130  "(do not reconfig, just re-start the sensor) valid\n");
131  return -1;
132  }
133  }
134  else
135  {
136  /* In case there is no argument for sensorStart, always do reconfig */
137  doReconfig = true;
138  }
139 
140  /***********************************************************************************
141  * Do sensor state management to influence the sensor actions
142  ***********************************************************************************/
143 
144  if ((gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_INIT) && (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState() == 0))
145  {
146  CLI_write ("Error: Full configuration must be provided before sensor can be started "
147  "the first time\n");
148  return -1;
149  }
150 
151  if (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_STARTED)
152  {
153  CLI_write ("Ignored: Sensor is already started\n");
154  return 0;
155  }
156 
157  if (doReconfig == false)
158  {
159  /* User intends to issue sensor start without config, check if no
160  config was issued after stop and generate error if this is the case. */
161  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInNonPendingState() == 0)
162  {
163  /* Message user differently if all config was issued or partial config was
164  issued. */
165  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState())
166  {
167  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided complete new configuration, "
168  "issue \"sensorStart\" (without argument) if you want it to "
169  "take effect\n");
170  }
171  else
172  {
173  CLI_write ("Error: There should be no configuration between stop and this "
174  "command. Issue the full configuration and do \"sensorStart\" "
175  "OR reboot system, we cannot undo partial config\n");
176  }
177  return -1;
178  }
179  }
180  else
181  {
182  /* User intends to issue sensor start with full config, check if all config
183  was issued after stop and generate error if is the case. */
184  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState() == 0)
185  {
186  /* Message user differently if no config was issued or partial config was
187  issued. */
188  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInNonPendingState())
189  {
190  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided no configuration, "
191  "issue \"sensorStart 0\" OR provide "
192  "full configuration and issue \"sensorStart\"\n");
193  }
194  else
195  {
196  CLI_write ("Error: Entire configuration must be provided, partial "
197  "configuration is not allowed. Issue the full configuration "
198  "and do \"sensorStart\" OR reboot system, we cannot undo "
199  "partial config\n");
200  }
201  return -1;
202  }
203  }
204 
205  /***********************************************************************************
206  * Retreive and check mmwave Open related config before calling openSensor
207  ***********************************************************************************/
208 
209  /* Fill demo's MCB mmWave openCfg structure from the CLI configs*/
210  if (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_INIT)
211  {
212  /* Get the open configuration: */
213  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionOpenConfig (&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg);
214  }
215  else
216  {
217  /* openCfg related configurations like chCfg, lowPowerMode, adcCfg
218  * are only used on the first sensor start. If they are different
219  * on a subsequent sensor start, then generate a fatal error
220  * so the user does not think that the new (changed) configuration
221  * takes effect, the board needs to be reboot for the new
222  * configuration to be applied.
223  */
224  MMWave_OpenCfg openCfg;
225  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionOpenConfig (&openCfg);
226  /* Compare openCfg->chCfg*/
227  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.chCfg, (void *)&openCfg.chCfg,
228  sizeof(rlChanCfg_t)) != 0)
229  {
230  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
231  }
232 
233  /* Compare openCfg->lowPowerMode*/
234  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.lowPowerMode, (void *)&openCfg.lowPowerMode,
235  sizeof(rlLowPowerModeCfg_t)) != 0)
236  {
237  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
238  }
239  /* Compare openCfg->adcOutCfg*/
240  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.adcOutCfg, (void *)&openCfg.adcOutCfg,
241  sizeof(rlAdcOutCfg_t)) != 0)
242  {
243  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
244  }
245  }
246 
247  retVal = MmwDemo_openSensor(gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_INIT);
248  if(retVal != 0)
249  {
250  return -1;
251  }
252 
253  /***********************************************************************************
254  * Retrieve mmwave Control related config before calling startSensor
255  ***********************************************************************************/
256  /* Get the mmWave ctrlCfg from the CLI mmWave Extension */
257  if(doReconfig)
258  {
259  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionConfig (&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.ctrlCfg);
260  retVal = MmwDemo_configSensor();
261  if(retVal != 0)
262  {
263  return -1;
264  }
265  }
266  retVal = MmwDemo_startSensor();
267  if(retVal != 0)
268  {
269  return -1;
270  }
271 
272  /***********************************************************************************
273  * Set the state
274  ***********************************************************************************/
275  gMmwMssMCB.sensorState = MmwDemo_SensorState_STARTED;
276  return 0;
277 }

294 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLISensorStop (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
295 {
296  if ((gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_STOPPED) ||
297  (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_INIT))
298  {
299  CLI_write ("Ignored: Sensor is already stopped\n");
300  return 0;
301  }
302 
303  MmwDemo_stopSensor();
304 
305  gMmwMssMCB.sensorState = MmwDemo_SensorState_STOPPED;
306  return 0;
307 }

324 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe (int32_t argc, char* argv[], int32_t expectedArgc,
325  int8_t* subFrameNum)
326 {
327  int8_t subframe;
328 
329  /* Sanity Check: Minimum argument check */
330  if (argc != expectedArgc)
331  {
332  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid usage of the CLI command\n");
333  return -1;
334  }
335 
336  /*Subframe info is always in position 1*/
337  subframe = (int8_t) atoi(argv[1]);
338 
339  if(subframe >= (int8_t)RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES)
340  {
341  CLI_write ("Error: Subframe number is invalid\n");
342  return -1;
343  }
344 
345  *subFrameNum = (int8_t)subframe;
346 
347  return 0;
348 }

409 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLICfarCfg (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
410 {
411  DPU_CFARCAProc_CfarCfg cfarCfg;
412  uint32_t procDirection;
413  int8_t subFrameNum;
414 
415  if(MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe(argc, argv, 10, &subFrameNum) < 0)
416  {
417  return -1;
418  }
419 
420  /* Initialize configuration: */
421  memset ((void *)&cfarCfg, 0, sizeof(cfarCfg));
422 
423  /* Populate configuration: */
424  procDirection = (uint32_t) atoi (argv[2]);
425  cfarCfg.averageMode = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[3]);
426  cfarCfg.winLen = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[4]);
427  cfarCfg.guardLen = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[5]);
428  cfarCfg.noiseDivShift = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[6]);
429  cfarCfg.cyclicMode = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[7]);
430  cfarCfg.thresholdScale = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[8]);
431  cfarCfg.peakGroupingEn = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[9]);
432 
433  /* Save Configuration to use later */
434  if (procDirection == 0)
435  {
436  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfarCfg, MMWDEMO_CFARCFGRANGE_OFFSET,
437  sizeof(cfarCfg), subFrameNum);
438  }
439  else
440  {
441  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfarCfg, MMWDEMO_CFARCFGDOPPLER_OFFSET,
442  sizeof(cfarCfg), subFrameNum);
443  }
444  return 0;
445 }

589 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLICalibDcRangeSig (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
590 {
591  DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg cfg;
592  uint32_t log2NumAvgChirps;
593  int8_t subFrameNum;
594 
595  if(MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe(argc, argv, 6, &subFrameNum) < 0)
596  {
597  return -1;
598  }
599 
600  /* Initialize configuration for DC range signature calibration */
601  memset ((void *)&cfg, 0, sizeof(cfg));
602 
603  /* Populate configuration: */
604  cfg.enabled = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[2]);
605  cfg.negativeBinIdx = (int16_t) atoi (argv[3]);
606  cfg.positiveBinIdx = (int16_t) atoi (argv[4]);
607  cfg.numAvgChirps = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[5]);
608 
609  if (cfg.negativeBinIdx > 0)
610  {
611  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid negative bin index\n");
612  return -1;
613  }
614  if ((cfg.positiveBinIdx - cfg.negativeBinIdx + 1) > DPU_RANGEPROC_SIGNATURE_COMP_MAX_BIN_SIZE)
615  {
616  CLI_write ("Error: Number of bins exceeds the limit\n");
617  return -1;
618  }
619  log2NumAvgChirps = (uint32_t) mathUtils_ceilLog2(cfg.numAvgChirps);
620  if (cfg.numAvgChirps != (1U << log2NumAvgChirps))
621  {
622  CLI_write ("Error: Number of averaged chirps is not power of two\n");
623  return -1;
624  }
625 
626  /* Save Configuration to use later */
627  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfg, MMWDEMO_CALIBDCRANGESIG_OFFSET,
628  sizeof(cfg), subFrameNum);
629 
630  return 0;
631 }

728 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLICompRangeBiasAndRxChanPhaseCfg (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
729 {
730  DPU_AoAProc_compRxChannelBiasCfg cfg;
731  int32_t Re, Im;
732  int32_t argInd;
733  int32_t i;
734 
735  /* Sanity Check: Minimum argument check */
736  if (argc != (1+1+SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS*SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL*2))
737  {
738  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid usage of the CLI command\n");
739  return -1;
740  }
741 
742  /* Initialize configuration: */
743  memset ((void *)&cfg, 0, sizeof(cfg));
744 
745  /* Populate configuration: */
746  cfg.rangeBias = (float) atof (argv[1]);
747 
748  argInd = 2;
749  for (i=0; i < SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS*SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL; i++)
750  {
751  Re = (int32_t) (atof (argv[argInd++]) * 32768.);
752  MATHUTILS_SATURATE16(Re);
753  cfg.rxChPhaseComp[i].real = (int16_t) Re;
754 
755  Im = (int32_t) (atof (argv[argInd++]) * 32768.);
756  MATHUTILS_SATURATE16(Im);
757  cfg.rxChPhaseComp[i].imag = (int16_t) Im;
758 
759  }
760  /* Save Configuration to use later */
761  memcpy((void *) &gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.compRxChanCfg,
762  &cfg, sizeof(cfg));
763 
764  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.isCompRxChannelBiasCfgPending = 1;
765 
766  return 0;
767 }

821 void MmwDemo_CLIInit (uint8_t taskPriority)
822 {
823  CLI_Cfg cliCfg;
824  char demoBanner[256];
825  uint32_t cnt;
826 
827  /* Create Demo Banner to be printed out by CLI */
828  sprintf(&demoBanner[0],
829  "******************************************\n" \
830  "xWR18xx MMW Demo %02d.%02d.%02d.%02d\n" \
831  "******************************************\n",
832  MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MAJOR,
833  MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MINOR,
834  MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUGFIX,
835  MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUILD
836  );
837 
838  /* Initialize the CLI configuration: */
839  memset ((void *)&cliCfg, 0, sizeof(CLI_Cfg));
840 
841  /* Populate the CLI configuration: */
842  cliCfg.cliPrompt = "mmwDemo:/>";
843  cliCfg.cliBanner = demoBanner;
844  cliCfg.cliUartHandle = gMmwMssMCB.commandUartHandle;
